Peru Says Grana y Montero, Ferrovias Win Lima Railway Contract

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-02-22T23:39:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/peru-says-grana-y-montero-ferrovias-win-lima-railway-contract.html
  Grana y Montero SA , the Peruvian
construction company, and partner Ferrovias SA won a 652 million
soles ($235 million) contract to operate  Lima ’s overhead  railway 
and supply it with trains, the government said.  The railway, which is being extended by Grana and  Brazil ’s
Odebrecht SA, is expected to carry 1 million passengers a day,
the government’s private investment promotion agency
Proinversion said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Faries at 
 wfaries@bloomberg.net  